*Assessment*

_NoEcho_ property in _Parameters_ declaration is not honored the same as in euform-describe-stacks compared to cfn-describe-stacks.  From the AWS documentation regarding the [_Parameters_ declaration|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/parameters-section-structure.html], the _NoEcho_  property is defined as follows:
{quote}
NoEcho

If TRUE, the value of the parameter is masked with asterisks (*****) with aws cloudformation describe-stacks.
{quote}
Even though the response back from the server shows the value of the parameter not in asterisks (***), euform-describe-stacks --show-long fails to show that information in its output.

*Signs*

* _Parameters_ declaration:
{code}
    "Parameters": {
        "UbuntuImageId": {
            "Description":"Ubuntu Image id",
            "Type":"String",
            "NoEcho":"False"
        },

        "Acct1User01KeyPair": {
            "Description":"Account1 User01 Key Pair",
            "Type":"String",
            "NoEcho":"False"
        }
    },
{code}

* output from euform-describe-stacks --show-long:
{code}
# euform-describe-stacks --show-long --region account1-user01@
